{{Primary sources|date=June 2011}} '''Knowland''' is a web-based [[software company]] that provides [[business development]] products and services to the [[hospitality industry]].
==History== Knowland traces its roots back to a small [[software engineering]] firm. This firm spent months developing an entirely new kind of hotel readerboard service, heavily reliant on web technology, for a client in the industry. When the client backed out, Knowland’s founders recognized the hospitality industry’s need for a higher standard of market intelligence. They decided to start their own hospitality [[field research]] service, and by the fall of 2004 an online readerboard service was launched.{{Citation needed|date=September 2012}}
Knowland signed its first client, the [[Holiday Inn]] in [[Arlington, Virginia|Arlington, Va.]], in September 2004.<ref name="auto">[https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2010/08/29/AR2010082902450_2.html?nav=rss_opinion/columns "Knowland Group became one of the fastest-growing companies by taking photos of signs."] ''[[The Washington Post]]''. Retrieved 2011-05-11.</ref> During 2005, the company expanded to over 20 markets, serving a diverse clientele of single and multi-property clients. By the end of 2006, Knowland had over 400 clients in 60 markets and had tracked more than 200,000 events.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hotel-online.com/News/PR2007_1st/Jan07_Knowland.html|title=Market Intelligence Firm Celebrates Tremendous Growth; Knowland Tracks Details on over 247,000 Events in 2006, Revenue Grows 548% in Second Full Year of Operations, Now in Over 60 Metropolitan Areas / January 2007|first=Richard L.|last=Johnson|website=Hotel-online.com|accessdate=9 August 2017}}</ref>
In 2007, Knowland introduced Insight, a tool that generates targeted [[sales lead]]s with details on each prospect’s event booking history.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hotel-online.com/News/PR2007_3rd/Sept07_KnowlandInsight.html|title=Knowland Unleashes INSIGHT on the World of Hospitality and Asks Hoteliers to Imagine... Imagine a breakthrough tool that provides access to over $3 billon In group bookings|date=September 2007|first=Richard L.|last=Johnson|website=Hotel-online.com|accessdate=9 August 2017}}</ref> The company also activated a 7,000 square foot [[call center]] to expand its infrastructure for customer support, in-depth contact and event research, and sales activities on behalf of customers. The Event Booking Center employs research and sales support professionals who specialize in [[cold calling]] and can become an extension of hotel clients’ sales staff.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hotel-online.com/News/PR2007_3rd/July07_KnowlandCenter.html|title=The Knowland Group Opens 100 Seat Call Center in Salisbury MD; Market Intelligence Firm Continues Expansion, Opens Combined Call, Operations Center on Maryland's Eastern Shore / July 2007|first=Richard L.|last=Johnson|website=Hotel-online.com|accessdate=9 August 2017}}</ref>
Knowland launched Target Net, a meetings management and sales force [[automation]] platform, in 2010. In addition to managing events from start to finish, Target Net also generated sales leads and opportunities.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.knowland.com/data/PDFBase/and%20Group%20Launches%20TargetNet129089905378038750.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-10-06 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141009001811/http://www.knowland.com/data/PDFBase/and%20Group%20Launches%20TargetNet129089905378038750.pdf |archivedate=2014-10-09 |df= }} </ref> This product was discontinued in 2015.
Today Knowland is a provider of intuitive business intelligence products for the hospitality industry and has more than 3,000 client [[hotel]]s and 50,000 users globally.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cms.knowland.com/data/PDFBase/Group_Announces_New_President_and_CEO_Tim_Hart.pdf|format=PDF|title=The Knowland Group Announces New President and Chief Executive Officer, Tim Hart|website=Cms.knowland.com|accessdate=2014-10-06}}</ref>
==Products== {{Advertisement|section|date=March 2016}}
Knowland is a provider of business development solutions to the hospitality industry. Target Net, Insight, and Readers are [[Cloud computing|cloud-based]] and accessible from any computer connected to the [[Internet]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hotel-online.com/News/PR2010_4th/Oct10_KnowlandCloud.html|title=Knowland Moves Reports to the Cloud; Innovative Business Development Firm Enhances Client Experience / October 2010|first=Richard L.|last=Johnson|website=Hotel-online.com|accessdate=9 August 2017}}</ref>
===Target Net=== Target Net is a salesforce automation and meetings management tool that allows [[hotel manager|hoteliers]] to manage their [[sales funnel]] from start to finish.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://dc.citybizlist.com/5/2011/2/3/Target-Net-Goes-Mobile-On-the-iPad.aspx |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2011-05-12 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110814093030/http://dc.citybizlist.com/5/2011/2/3/Target-Net-Goes-Mobile-On-the-iPad.aspx |archivedate=2011-08-14 |df= }} Retrieved 2011-05-12.</ref>
Knowland no longer sells Target Net product, but continues to offer support for clients already using it.{{citation needed|date=March 2015}}
===Insight=== Insight is a [[search engine]] and sales lead-generation tool that gives hotel sales teams access to a database of groups that have held millions of meetings at hotels and [[conference center]]s.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hotelnewsresource.com/article51480Knowland_Gives_Hoteliers_New_Insight_into_Business_Development.html|title=Knowland Gives Hoteliers New Insight into Business Development|first=Hotel News|last=Resource|website=Hotelnewsresource.com|accessdate=9 August 2017}}</ref>
In 2014, Knowland released Insight 3.0, an effort to enhance the Insight platform, which transformed the traditional search engine leads database into a customizable meeting intelligence tool for event professionals. Insight 3.0 included new features such as anonymous reviews of groups and their events, the ability to follow groups, properties, and people, and more detailed group profiles.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.knowland.com/content/insight|title=Insight|date=11 December 2015|website=Knowland.com|accessdate=9 August 2017}}</ref>
After receiving many unfavorable reviews from clients regarding the changes to Insight for the 3.0 release, Knowland launched Insight 3.1 the following year (2015). Insight 3.1 was designed almost entirely around user feedback. This release leveraged the powerful, and once again enhanced, search capabilities of the tool, putting popular search features in the spotlight. Insight 3.1 made the focus of Knowland technology less about social media-influenced networking and more about the power of its raw, historical data on groups, planners, meetings, and contact information to help clients optimize their sales tactics.
===Readers=== Readers is an online readerboard service that offers daily reporting and data on groups that hold meetings and events at hotels' competitor properties. Readers combines an online tool with Knowland’s version of a traditional readerboard report, in addition to telephone-verified contact information. Each week, approximately 400 field researchers<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.e-hospitality.com/article.mvc/Knowland-Group-Introduces-Its-Business-0001|title=Knowland Group Introduces Its Business Development Suite For The Hospitality Industry|website=E-hospitality.com|accessdate=9 August 2017}}</ref> take [[Digital photography|digital photos]] of hotel readerboards. Those photos are uploaded each night to the Knowland database and the data made available online to clients the next morning. New groups are constantly being added to the [[database]] and detailed profiles are created and updated for each group.<ref name="auto"/> In April 2014, Knowland released a new data management process to help maintain the accuracy and freshness of the information provided.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.knowland.com/data/PDFBase/That_Helps_Keep_Information_Fresh_and_Accurate.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-10-06 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141008215318/http://www.knowland.com/data/PDFBase/That_Helps_Keep_Information_Fresh_and_Accurate.pdf |archivedate=2014-10-08 |df= }} </ref>
==Recognition== Knowland Group was ranked 26th on [[Deloitte]]’s [[Deloitte Fast 500|2010 Technology Fast 500™]] list in October 2010.<ref>[http://www.hospitalitynet.org/news/154000320/4048779.html "Deloitte Fast 500™ Technology List Ranks Knowland 26th Overall, 5th in Software, 1st in Region."] Hospitality Net. Retrieved 2011-07-14.</ref> The list identifies the fastest-growing technology, media, telecommunications, life sciences, and clean technology companies in [[North America]]. Rankings for the award were based on the fiscal revenue growth from 2005–2009, during which Knowland grew 5,764 percent.<ref>[http://www.deloitte.com/assets/Dcom-UnitedStates/Local%20Assets/Documents/TMT_us_tmt/us_tmt_2010%20Technology%20Fast%20500%20Winners%20Brochure_191010.pdf "Deloitte's 2010 Technology Fast 500"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120319211227/http://www.deloitte.com/assets/Dcom-UnitedStates/Local%20Assets/Documents/TMT_us_tmt/us_tmt_2010%20Technology%20Fast%20500%20Winners%20Brochure_191010.pdf |date=2012-03-19 }} Deloitte. Retrieved 2011-07-14.</ref> Knowland ranked fifth out of 190 companies in the software industry, which was the largest industry recognized on the [[Fast 500]]™ list. Knowland ranked first on the [[Greater Philadelphia]] Fast 50 list.
Target Net, Knowland’s sales force automation and meetings management tool, received a 2010 Product of the Year Award from [[Technology Marketing Corporation]]’s Customer Interaction Solutions magazine.<ref>[http://www.allbusiness.com/company-activities-management/operations-customer/15511725-1.html] {{dead link|date=May 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> The award is given annually to companies based on their vision, leadership, and diligence.
