{{Infobox file format | name = QFX | icon = | logo = | screenshot = | caption = | extension = <tt>.qfx</tt> | mime = | type code = | uniform type = | magic = | owner = [[Intuit]] | released = | latest release version = | latest release date = | genre = | container for = [[Finance|Financial information]] | contained by = | extended from = [[Open Financial Exchange]] | extended to = | standard = | url = }} '''QFX''' is [[Intuit]]'s proprietary version of the standard [[Open Financial Exchange|OFX]] financial interchange [[file format]]. QFX is used in [[Intuit]]'s "Web Connect" and "Direct Connect" features to transmit and receive financial information over the internet.<ref>[http://www.file-extensions.org/qfx-file-extension QFX file extension at File-Extensions.org library]</ref><ref>[http://financialsoft.about.com/od/financialsoftwareglossary/g/def_QFX.htm about.com]</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Intuit's Direct Connect Developer Site |url=http://fi.intuit.com/whyconnect/FAQs/}}</ref>
A '''QFX''' file is a standard [[Open Financial Exchange|OFX]] file with additional fields to support a licensing fee paid by institutions to [[Intuit]]. In contrast, the standard OFX format is a free and [[open standard]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ofx.net/faq.html|title=Official OFX FAQ|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|accessdate=2018-09-21}}</ref> Intuit's [[Quicken]] software will only import QFX files where the providing institution has paid the fee and in some cases passed quality tests, otherwise giving the error message "Quicken is currently unable to verify the financial institution information for this download".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zdnet.com/news/customers-bemoan-changes-in-quicken-2005/138323 |title=Customers bemoan changes in Quicken 2005 |accessdate=2009-02-09 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boingboing.net/2005/01/29/quicken-disables-the.html |title=Quicken Disabled QIF In Favor of QFX |accessdate=2009-02-09 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Intuit Help For QFX Import Failure |url=http://web.intuit.com/support/quicken/2000/win/569878.html|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110824002051/http://web.intuit.com/support/quicken/2000/win/569878.html|archivedate = August 24, 2011|deadurl = yes}}</ref> The same error message is given for Quicken users attempting to import previously downloaded QFX files with non-supported versions of Quicken (i.e. Quicken 2011 and earlier).
